1 portion","576 kJ \/ 138 kcal","12 g","2 g","9 g"],"hintsAndTricks":["Steam in any heat-resistant cup or small bowl of similar size. If your dishes are a different size or they are not ceramic, you may have to adjust the cooking time. Once you know the perfect cooking time for your own dishes, make a note of it for next time.","Dashi, or Japanese cooking stock, adds flavour to the chawan mushi. You can replace the instant dashi powder with <b>½ tsp homemade<b> chicken or vegetable stock paste: first dilute the stock paste in some of the water before adding it in <b>step 1,<b> and reduce salt to <b>¼ tsp.<b> Or omit dashi powder and use <b>300 g stock<b> instead of water in <b>step 1.<b> Finally you can omit the dashi powder altogether; the dish will have a more subtle egg flavour."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","35m","6 portions"]}